✅ STAR Script 1 — Conflict with Stakeholder (Foveation Design)
Situation

I was reviewing a proposed foveated rendering design for an XR product where the GPU team suggested processing three identical camera streams and doing cropping and downscaling entirely on GPU.

Task

I was responsible for ensuring the solution delivered optimal performance and stability without increasing system cost.

Action

Reviewed the design deeply and proposed an alternate architecture where the camera subsystem performs cropping and downscaling, and GPU only stitches

Faced resistance because stakeholders believed this would increase CPU cycles

Collected performance benchmarks for both approaches using profiling tools

Added stability testing scenarios reflecting real user movement patterns

Engaged stakeholders using data and customer usage patterns to align on priorities

Result

Hybrid approach was adopted: GPU handles static scenarios; camera handles motion scenarios

Achieved ~15% CPU reduction in motion cases while maintaining performance

Improved stability significantly in real usage conditions

Solution deployed to production and appreciated by the client

Successfully resolved conflict through data-driven collaboration

Leadership Principles Shown: Dive Deep, Ownership, Earn Trust, Customer Obsession, Deliver Results


